description:
&lt;p&gt;The Planned Care Division are seeking a motivated and enthusiastic Service Manager to join their team to cover a maternity leave post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your roles and responsibilities will include ensuring that national standards and objectives are met, ensuring that you support the Division to remain within its financial threshold, as well as leading on quality improvement plans, providing clear and consistent leadership to staff and the teams you manage and you will also participate in the Senior Manager On-site Rota (SMOS) with on-call responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Service Manager, under guidance from the General Manager will take operational responsibility for the implementation of service developments and transformation initiatives. You will also be expected to deputise for the General Manager as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be a great team player, be highly organised and adaptable with the ability to work to tight timescales, whilst remaining reliable under pressure, motivated and willing to make a difference. If you share our commitment of putting patients first and feel you can take on the challenge of this high-profile role then we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proposed interview date: Week Commencing 30-Nov-2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dawn Jones, Divisional PA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : djones20@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01438286133&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Dawn Jones - Divisional PA to arrange an informal chat or visit&lt;/p&gt;
